<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="993" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                    <head>Government of the Canton of Valais</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="italic">The grand council of the canton of Valais to the legation
                            of the United States of America in Berne</hi>.</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The grand council joins in the addresses of
                        sympathy and condolence sent to the legation by the government of Valais,
                        and other states of the Swiss Confederation, on the subject of the
                        assassination of President Lincoln. The grand council is convinced that this
                        is the expression of the sentiments of the inhabitants of the canton.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">Given at <placeName>Sion</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-17">May 17, 1865</date>, in the
                            name of the grand council.</dateline>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>ZERMATTEN, <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                                <item>Z. DURIER,</item>
                                <item>L. E. ROURY, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Secretaries</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>